comments: Murray (DEN) legally contests Bogdanovic's (DET) jump shot attempt.
Jokic (DEN) takes an extra step and delivers leg to leg contact to Joseph (DET) which affects his ability to defend.
Duren (DET) jumps alongside Murray's (DEN) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Gordon (DEN) initiates contact with Burks' (DET) body, which affects his driving shot attempt.

Burks (DET) is moving alongside Caldwell-Pope's (DEN) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive. Both players mutually engage in incidental foot to foot contact as Caldwell-Pope releases away.
Gordon's (DEN) shot does not hit the rim before the shot clock expires.
Duren (DET) establishes himself in Murray's (DEN) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Joseph (DET) slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.

Burks (DET) goes to, not through, Murray (DEN) and incidental head contact occurs as they come together at the start of the drive. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Joseph (DET) initiates body contact with Jokic (DEN) that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Burks (DET) lifts and re-plants his pivot foot without releasing the ball.
Knox II (DET) extends both hands forward and initiates contact with Jokic (DEN) as he receives the pass.
Knox II (DET) immediately slides his hand off of Jokic's (DEN) side and marginal contact occurs off-ball in the post.
Knox II (DET) moves alongside Jokic's (DEN) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Gordon (DEN) commits a take foul on Bogdanovic (DET).
Porter Jr. (DEN) establishes himself in a wide screening position and delivers leg to leg contact with Joseph (DET) which affects his ability to defend.
Nnaji (DEN) dislodges Bagley III (DET) from his rebounding position, which affects his ability to pursue the loose ball.
Bogdanovic (DET) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Gordon's (DEN) arm.
Joseph (DET) initiates contact with Murray (DEN) that affects Murray's SQBR as the pick is set.
